  "response": "The profitability of food trucks can vary widely, but here are some general insights:\n\n1. Average Annual Revenue\n- Small food trucks: $100,000 - $250,000\n- Successful food trucks: $250,000 - $500,000\n- Top performing trucks: $500,000 - $1 million\n\n2. Profit Margins\n- Typical profit margins range from 6% to 20%\n- Average profit around 7-10%\n\n3. Factors Affecting Profitability\n- Location\n- Menu pricing\n- Food costs\n- Labor expenses\n- Marketing\n- Local competition\n- Event opportunities\n- Operating expenses\n\n4. Startup Costs\n- Initial investment: $50,000 - $175,000\n- Includes truck purchase/lease, equipment, permits, initial inventory\n\n5. Advantages\n- Lower overhead compared to traditional restaurants\n- More mobility and flexibility\n- Lower initial investment\n- Potential for multiple revenue streams\n\n6. Challenges\n- High competition\n- Variable income\n- Weather dependence\n- Complex regulations\n- Maintenance costs\n\nProfitability depends on individual business strategy, management, and local market conditions.",
